  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Preschool/Infant Teacher",
  "description": "<p><strong>Company Overview</strong><br>\nWe are a nurturing and dynamic preschool dedicated to providing a safe, engaging, and holistic learning environment for young children. We believe in developing each child’s potential through quality care, purposeful play, and strong partnerships with families.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong><br>\n• Plan, supervise, and implement class programmes in accordance with the centre’s policies and curriculum framework.<br>\n• Prepare progress reports and developmental portfolios for each child every semester.<br>\n• Create a stimulating and engaging learning environment that encourages self-directed learning.<br>\n• Manage classroom activities and ensure children’s safety, hygiene, and well-being at all times.<br>\n• Work collaboratively with other teaching staff to deliver quality early childhood education.<br>\n• Build and maintain strong, positive relationships with parents and caregivers.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong><br>\n• Minimum <strong>Diploma in Early Childhood Care and Education</strong><br>\n• <strong>ECDA L2 Certification</strong><br>\n• Excellent communication and interpersonal skills<br>\n• At least 2<strong> year of relevant experience</strong> in a preschool environment (preferred)<br>\n• High tolerance and genuine passion for working with children<br>\n• Able to work both <strong>independently</strong> and <strong>as part of a team</strong></p>",
